Tinkatink

Evolves At 5

Tinkatuff

Evolves At 7

Mold Breaker

Passive Ability

When damaging an opposing Pokémon with an active shield effect, 30% of the damage dealt to the shield is dealt as additional damage to the target's HP.

This Pokémon's hammer strengthens every time they hit Pokémon from the opposing team with boosted attacks or moves, increasing this Pokémon's Attack by 0.5% per target hit (up to 60 times; maximum 30% Attack). After the hammer is strengthened 20, 40, and 60 times; Rock Smash, Gigaton Hammer, and Smack Down gain increased range.

Attack

Auto Attack

Becomes a boosted attack after 12s, swinging the user's hammer in a circle around them, dealing increased damage and restoring 20% of the user's missing HP when it hits. This boosted attack remains readied until used. The time until the next boosted attack is readied is reduced faster when hit by opposing Pokémon's auto attacks.

The hammer's size and basic attack range increase upon evolving into Tinkatuff and into Tinkaton.

100% Atk + 0 x (Level - 1) + 0

180% Atk + 60 x (Level - 1) + 0

Rock Smash

Move 1

6.50s Melee

The user swings down their hammer with rock-crushing force, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect and stunning them for 0.15s when hit.

The stronger the hammer, the larger this move's area of effect.

160% Atk + 10 x (Level - 1) + 350

Rock Smash Upgrade Choices

Gigaton Hammer

6.00s Melee

The user becomes unstoppable and decreases their movement speed by 50% as they charge power for up to 1.95s, becoming fully charged after 1s, before swinging down their hammer in the designated direction, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect and throwing them when hit. This move deals more damage and the throw duration is strengthened the longer it is charged.

The stronger the hammer, the larger this move's area of effect.

Throw duration: 0.5s
168% Atk + 12 x (Level - 1) + 260

Throw duration: 1s
294% Atk + 21 x (Level - 1) + 454

Throw duration: 1.5s
420% Atk + 30 x (Level - 1) + 650

Reduces this move's cooldown by 1s.

Smack Down

6.00s Ranged

The user charges power for up to 2.4s, becoming fully charged after 0.8s, then uses their hammer to send a rock flying to the designated area, damaging opposing Pokémon at the rock's point of impact and decreasing the movement speed of those hit by 50% for 3s (decaying by 10% every 0.5s). The longer this move is charged, the farther the rock can fly. This move deals increased damage at maximum charge. If this move is canceled, it goes on a 2s cooldown.

The stronger the hammer, the larger this move's maximum range.

225% Atk + 22 x (Level - 1) + 540

300% Atk + 30 x (Level - 1) + 720

Reduces this move's cooldown by 1s.

Fairy Wind

Move 2

6.00s Ranged

The user stirs up a fairy wind in the designated direction, damaging opposing Pokémon hit and decreasing their movement speed by 20% for 1s.

100% Atk + 8 x (Level - 1) + 200

Fairy Wind Upgrade Choices

Ice Hammer

5.00s Dash

The user leaps in the designated direction and swings down their freezing hammer at the designated location, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect, decreasing the movement speed of those hit by 50%, their Attack by 30%, and their Sp. Atk by 15% for 2.5s.

100% Atk + 13 x (Level - 1) + 200

Strengthens the Attack decrease of opposing Pokémon hit to 50% and the Sp. Atk decrease to 30%.

Thief

7.00s Buff

Increases the user's movement speed by 25% for 3s, strengthened to 50% for 5s when moving toward an opposing Pokémon affected by hindrances; and empowers the user's next basic attack for 5s, swinging their hammer in front of them and dealing boosted attack damage to opposing Pokémon hit. If this Thief empowered basic attack hits a Pokémon from the opposing team, the user gains a Thief buff for 5s, increasing their Defense and Sp. Def by 10% per target hit (up to 5 times; maximum 50%). While the user has the Thief buff, the movement speed increases remain in effect; the user readies boosted attacks after 2s, and the time until the next boosted attack is reduced significantly when hit by opposing Pokémon's auto attacks.

Pokémon from the opposing team hit with Thief empowered basic attacks have a separate Thief debuff applied to them for 5s, decreasing their Defense and Sp. Def by 10%. The duration of the Thief debuff on targets hit refreshes when hit by subsequent Thief empowered attacks, and the duration of the Thief buff on the user is refreshed when a Pokémon from the opposing team is hit with the empowered attack.

180% Atk + 60 x (Level - 1) + 0

Strengthens the Defense and Sp. Def decrease on targets hit by the empowered auto attack to 25%; strengthens the Defense and Sp. Def increases on the user to 25% per target hit (maximum 125%).

Kiss Bliss Kaboom

Unite Move

89s 80000 Sure Hit

Unlocks at level 9

The user first blows cute kisses at the designated Pokémon from the opposing team and their nearby allies, damaging and stunning them for 0.7s when Kiss Bliss hits a target. The user can then use the Unite Move again, leaping up forward and slamming their hammer down at the designated location, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect of Kaboom.

Unite Move buffs apply when Kiss Bliss hits a target.

50% Atk + 3 x (Level - 1) + 100

250% Atk + 22 x (Level - 1) + 700

Unite Buffs (6s duration):

30% Movement Speed, 30% CDR, 20% Max HP Shield
